parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body can cause the engine to stall, lose power, and accelerate erratically, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Unable to accelerate
engine stalling
sudden loss of power
strange growling or humming noise from the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping and jerking can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or accelerate erratically, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Transmission jerking or slipping while shifting gears
whining noise when climbing hills or traveling on highways
engine revving up to 3000 RPM.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or fail to shift gears, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission overheating can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or accelerate erratically, leading to potential accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Transmission overheating warning light
loss of power
deceleration
whining noise from the transmission.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Body Control and Computer Glitch
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The throttle body control and computer glitch can cause the vehicle to have acceleration issues, leading to a loss of power and potentially causing accidents, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle refuses to increase in speed while driving
the throttle body control light and check engine light come on
the vehicle has a sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The head rest failure can cause injury to the passenger, especially if it occurs while driving.
symptoms: The head rest pops open while driving
causing discomfort and potential injury to the passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating and engine shutdown can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle overheats
the engine shuts down
the vehicle stalls in normal traffic.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration can cause accidents, especially if the vehicle is on the highway or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates
even when the brake pedal is pressed
the vehicle rolls forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The electrical and mechanical issues can cause a range of problems, including difficulty starting the vehicle, noise from the rear and front of the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents or breakdowns.
symptoms: The vehicle has difficulty starting
noise comes from the rear and front of the vehicle
the vehicle has a tendency to not start when it's supposed to.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Window Defroster and Embedded Wiper Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rear window defroster and embedded wiper failure can cause the rear window to explode, potentially causing injury or damage.
symptoms: The rear window explodes after using the rear window defroster
the embedded wiper is damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or become inoperable, leading to safety risks, especially when the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The vehicle stops suddenly
fails to start
warning indicators illuminate on the instrument panel
hazard lights do not function
doors and trunk may not unlock
and the vehicle may become immovable.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sunroof leak can cause water to accumulate in the electrical controls, leading to random opening of the sunroof, and potentially causing electrical shorts, which can lead to safety risks.
symptoms: Water leaks from the map lights when it rains
causing water to dump onto the occupants and vehicle controls
and the sunroof may open randomly due to water buildup.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the blower motor can cause reduced visibility while driving, especially in rapidly changing climates, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: The blower motor fails without notice
resulting in a foggy windshield
lack of defrost feature
and de-ice features
and sudden restricted vision.
